---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
    title="Terms of Service & Usage License | Laravel Mail"
    description="Review the terms of service and usage license for Laravel Mail. Understand your rights, responsibilities, and our legal framework for self-hosted marketing services."
>
    <main class="py-20 px-6 sm:px-8 lg:px-12 max-w-7xl mx-auto">
        <div class="prose prose-slate max-w-3xl mx-auto">
            <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Terms of Use</h1>

            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
                Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString()}
            </p>

            <section class="mb-8">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">
                    1. Agreement to Terms
                </h2>
                <p>
                    By accessing and using Laravel Mail’s platform and services,
                    you agree to be bound by these Terms of Use and all
                    applicable laws and regulations. If you do not agree with
                    these terms, you must not use our services.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-8">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">2. Use License</h2>
                <p>
                    We grant you a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable
                    license to access and use Laravel Mail for personal or
                    business email management in accordance with these Terms.
                    Under this license you may not:
                </p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-4">
                    <li>
                        Modify, copy, or redistribute any part of the platform
                        without authorization
                    </li>
                    <li>Use the services for unlawful or harmful purposes</li>
                    <li>
                        Attempt to reverse engineer, decompile, or otherwise
                        access the source code
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Remove or alter any copyright or proprietary notices
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Transfer your account or mirror our platform without
                        permission
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-8 font-bold">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-brand-primary">
                    3. Refund Policy
                </h2>
                <p>
                    Due to the nature of Laravel Mail being a digital software
                    product with accessible source code and immediate delivery, <b
                        >no refunds</b
                    > will be issued once the purchase is completed. By completing
                    your purchase, you acknowledge and agree that you waive your right
                    to a refund or withdrawal period.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-8">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">4. Disclaimer</h2>
                <p>
                    Laravel Mail is provided on an "as is" and "as available"
                    basis. We disclaim all warranties, express or implied,
                    including but not limited to merchantability, fitness for a
                    particular purpose, and non-infringement. We do not
                    guarantee uninterrupted or error-free operation.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-8">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">
                    5. Limitations of Liability
                </h2>
                <p>
                    To the maximum extent permitted by law, Laravel Mail and its
                    affiliates shall not be held liable for any indirect,
                    incidental, or consequential damages, including but not
                    limited to loss of data, profits, or business opportunities,
                    arising from your use of or inability to use our services.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-8">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">
                    6. Accuracy of Information
                </h2>
                <p>
                    While we strive to provide accurate and up-to-date
                    information, Laravel Mail does not warrant that the content
                    on our platform is free from errors or omissions. We may
                    update or change content at any time without notice.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-8">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">
                    7. Third-Party Links
                </h2>
                <p>
                    Laravel Mail may contain links to third-party websites. We
                    are not responsible for the content, security, or practices
                    of any linked sites. Accessing such websites is at your own
                    risk.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-8">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">8. Modifications</h2>
                <p>
                    We reserve the right to revise these Terms of Use at any
                    time. By continuing to use Laravel Mail after changes are
                    posted, you agree to the updated version of the terms.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-8">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">9. Governing Law</h2>
                <p>
                    These Terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance
                    with the laws of England and Wales. You agree to submit to
                    the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of London, UK.
                </p>
            </section>
        </div>
    </main>
</Layout>
